## v1.3.0 (2026-06-20)

**Changed by:** Plan R2 (re-planning, post-NOGO) learning from issue #154 (Argus dashboard distroless healthcheck) — Odysseus session
**Verification:** unverified (planning learning only; no code run, no CI). The distroless binary self-probe pattern is NOT tested — it is a plan-derived correction.

### What changed
- Bumped version 1.2.0 → 1.3.0 (MINOR — new Failed-Attempts rows + a new clearly-flagged unverified subsection under "Compose Healthchecks" + new reviewer-risk bullets; no breaking removals)
- Bumped `date` 2026-06-19 → 2026-06-20; kept `history` frontmatter field; `verification: unverified` retained (overall)
- Added 3 new Failed Attempts rows from the R2 distroless-healthcheck learning: `wget` healthcheck against a distroless app image (no shell/wget/busybox in distroless static); trusting `docker compose config` as proof the healthcheck works (config validates structure only, never runs the probe); "matches every existing service" reasoning (convention only transfers within the same base-image family)
- Added a new subsection under **"Compose Healthchecks"** titled **"Distroless app images — binary self-probe healthcheck (planning learning, unverified)"** with the binary self-probe pattern `["CMD","/<binary>","-healthcheck"]`, the cross-issue coordination note (the `-healthcheck` flag may be owned by a different issue/PR), and verification discipline (assert no shell-out to wget/sh; post-build assert the container actually reaches `healthy`)
- Added reviewer-risk / planning meta-lessons (flagged unverified): check the TARGET service's runtime base image before copying a sibling's healthcheck; `docker compose config` passing is NOT evidence a healthcheck works; the self-probe introduces a cross-issue coordination dependency on the `-healthcheck` flag; an issue body's verbatim YAML is a desired end-state, not a guaranteed-correct literal (re-derive correctness from the actual base image)

### Why
A Compose/Docker healthcheck that shells out to `wget`/`curl` is BROKEN against a
`gcr.io/distroless/static-*` runtime image — distroless `static` images contain ONLY the static
binary (no shell, no wget, no busybox). The failure mode is SILENT: `docker compose config` passes
structural validation (so a plan whose only health verification is `compose config` is green) while
the deployed container never reaches `healthy` and the acceptance criterion fails post-merge. The
distroless-safe pattern is a binary self-probe `["CMD","/<binary>","-healthcheck"]` — Compose
healthchecks ALWAYS run inside the container, so there is no shell-free external-tool option. This
is the SAME topic surface as the skill's existing "Compose Healthchecks" section and its
`nats:latest` distroless Failed-Attempts row, so it was folded into this canonical skill rather than
spawning a new file. This is a planning learning (R0 plan got NOGO); the self-probe was NOT tested.

