### Why
The first plan (v1.1.0 amendment, PR #2592) was NOGO'd. The re-plan (R1) fixed the findings and,
critically, PROTOTYPED the validator this time instead of shipping unvalidated awk. The NOGO
surfaced five concrete latent traps — chief among them an awk parser that stopped at the first `}`
and thus closed the nested `tls{}` rather than `leafnodes{}`, mis-declaring a correctly-authed
config as unauthenticated. The durable learning is a refinement of the prior amendment (same topic,
same canonical skill): hard-won planning lessons that any NATS-leaf-auth (or config-block-gate) plan
in this ecosystem must apply — prototype the validator, track brace depth, test fail-closed, verify
the CI invocation graph, and assert negative paths in both directions.

