### Prior history of atlas-mesh-bringup-first-run

# atlas-mesh-bringup-first-run -- History

## v2.0.0 (2026-05-03)

**Changed by:** Full 6-host Tailnet cold-start session (2026-05-03)
**Verification:** verified-local -- executed end-to-end across 6 Tailnet hosts

### What changed
- Rewrote description and overview to cover multi-host cold-start (not just epimetheus single-host)
- Corrected binary names throughout: `ProjectAgamemnon_server` (NOT `agamemnon`), `ProjectNestor_server` (NOT `nestor`)
- Added NATS binary path fact: `~/.local/bin/nats-server` (not in PATH by default)
- Added Hermes src-layout requirement: must set `PYTHONPATH=src` before uvicorn
- Added `-DProjectAgamemnon_ENABLE_CLANG_TIDY=OFF` requirement for pixi conda toolchain builds (artemis)
- Added multi-host cold-start strategy table covering all 8 known Tailnet hosts with correct per-host method
- Added podman container build instructions for hosts without Odysseus
- Added native build flags for hephaestus (`-lz` for OpenSSL zlib dep) and artemis (pixi+clang-tidy off)
- Added docker path for apollo (Python 3.7 host -- too old for Hermes)
- Added confirmed Agamemnon API shape: health at `/health`, `{"service":"ProjectAgamemnon","status":"ok"}`, tasks at `POST /v1/teams/<id>/tasks`, completion via `PATCH .../tasks/<id>` (NOT POST .../complete)
- Added echo-type task clarification: requires external PATCH to complete (no autonomous executor)
- Added `.team.id` extraction note for team creation response
- Added Hermes Dockerfile bugs (PR #415): missing `prometheus_client`, wrong default `HERMES_PORT` (8080 vs 8085)
- Added 12 new Failed Attempts rows (binary names, PYTHONPATH, cmake/pixi, HERMES_PORT, prometheus_client, Python 3.7, fresh clone, -lz)
- Added 2026-05-03 session metrics and host reachability matrix
- Updated Verified On table with 2026-05-03 cold-start session

### Why
The v1.0.0 skill documented the first bringup on a single host (epimetheus) with Odysseus already
present. The 2026-05-03 multi-host cold-start revealed that:
1. Binary names are `ProjectAgamemnon_server` and `ProjectNestor_server` (not `agamemnon`/`nestor`)
2. NATS binary is not in PATH by default on remote hosts
3. Hermes requires `PYTHONPATH=src` (src-layout repo) and must use `hermes.server:app`
4. Three of 6 target hosts had no Odysseus clone -- fresh clone required before any service start
5. Agamemnon `POST .../complete` returns 404; the correct completion path is `PATCH .../tasks/<id>`
6. Two Hermes Dockerfile bugs (prometheus_client missing, HERMES_PORT default=8080) caused container failures

### Previous version (v1.0.0) snapshot

